This small town is great for walking along the shoreline of Lake Taneycomo and Fishing Island.  You can also get around by renting a boat from one of the many marinas.  Rollerblading up and down Main Street is a lot of fun too!

value: , Lake Taneycomo is a cold lake with water coming from the bottom of Table Rock lake, the temperature is around 55 degrees. Over night and early in the morning this causes a fog to develop over the lake creating an eerie scene.

You are located on the beach of Lake Taneycomo with some of the best trout fishing you will find anywhere. Catch Bass and Rainbow Trout from the town's very own Fishing Island. This complimentary island is walking distance over the bridge from the town's Main Street.  On the island there is a covered pavilion with picnic tables and cleaning stations for the fish that you catch.

You don't even have to bring a pole or boat. They are available for rent. Some of the places listed in "Sleep" have rentals available. Or you can fish from one of the public docks or along the shore. The state record for brown trout was caught in Bull Shoals Lake, just below Lake Taneycomo's Powersite Dam in 1997 and weighed 26 pounds, 13 ounces. It is know for sure there are larger trout in Lake Taneycomo. The Missouri Department of Conservation fisheries biologists during a sampling expedition, captured and quickly released a male brown trout that weighed about 37 pounds.

561-5410. The best catfish.  Very mild and not fishy at all.  Their pies and cobblers are delicious.  This place is located on the shore of lake Taneycomo.  You can enjoy the views of the lake while you dine. It's a nice scenic windy drive into town that you'll really enjoy.

561-4709 Just around the bend and up the hill from the boat launch ramp and fishing island. "The Cellar" as the locals call it, is exactly what it is... a real underground cellar. Just off the side of the road, and easy to miss there is an old door that opens up to a flight of stairs leading down to the bar/pizza restaurant. It's always dark, and usually full of smoke (especially at night), but the pizza makes it all worthwhile. It's also a good place to get a cold beer.
